Poor digital communication can often lead to misunderstandings and missed opportunities. For example, if a student sends an email to a professor without a proper subject line, greeting, or clear message, it may be ignored or considered unprofessional. This could result in delayed responses or even missed deadlines.
Such situations can be avoided by following proper email etiquette, including using a clear subject line, maintaining a polite tone, and structuring the message properly. This task helped me understand the importance of clear and professional communication in academic and professional environments.
